KGHM, Tauron Reach Shortlist for Niedzica Hydro Plant in Poland

-- B y   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 
2011-09-05T06:17:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/kghm-tauron-reach-shortlist-for-niedzica-hydro-plant-in-poland.html
A unit of  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH) ,
Poland’s sole copper producer, and  Tauron Polska Energia SA (TPE) , the
country’s second-largest power utility, were shortlisted to buy
the Niedzica hydroelectric plant, Poland’s Treasury Ministry
said on its website.  Energa SA, a Polish utility; Energo-Pro AS of the Czech
Republic; and a group including Kulczyk Holding SA were the
other shortlisted bidders, the ministry said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nathaniel Espino at 
 nespino@bloomberg.net  